e products ${I_\\rho}_{nm}{I_\\gamma}_{nm}$ and\n${O_\\rho}_{nm}{O_\\gamma}_{nm}$ are $B$-independent quantities. A dependence of\nthe measures on the ring geometry is discussed. It is argued that a variation\nof the position Shannon entropy or Onicescu energy with the AB field uniquely\ndetermines an associated persistent current as a function of $\\phi_{AB}$ at\n$B=0$. An inverse statement is correct too.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Dec 2018 11:19:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Mar 2019 00:17:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-08"}
